Program: Last Word
Title: George Baker, Ramiz Alia, Madeleine Simms and George Hinchcliffe
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b015pc07
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 16 Oct 2011
Matthew Bannister on The actor George Baker, best known for his TV portrayal of Inspector Wexford. The character's creator Baroness Ruth Rendell pays tribute; The former Albanian President Ramiz Alia who oversaw the country's transition from isolated Stalinism to democracy; Madeleine Simms who campaigned for the reform of abortion law in the 1960s; George Hinchcliffe the railway enthusiast who toured America with the Flying Scotsman; And the "Ghazal King" - Indian singer and composer Jagjit Singh. Show less